      <p>This policy explains cancellations and refunds for payments made through the Services. Online payments are processed by our payment gateway (Razorpay).</p>

      <h2>1. Subscription plans (schools)</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Subscriptions to Schoozie plans/modules are billed in advance for the chosen cycle.</li>
        <li>You may cancel a subscription at any time; cancellation stops future renewals. Access continues until the end of the paid period.</li>
        <li>Except where required by law or stated below, subscription fees already paid are non-refundable. Add-on / capacity packs are non-refundable once activated.</li>
        <li>If you believe you were charged in error or a service was not delivered, contact us within 7 days of the charge and we will investigate.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>2. School fees paid by parents</h2>
      <p>School fees (tuition, transport, hostel, etc.) are set and collected by the school, not by Schoozie. Schoozie only facilitates the online payment. Any refund of school fees is decided by the school as per its own refund rules. For fee refunds, please contact your school directly; we will support the school in processing an approved refund.</p>

      <h2>3. Failed or duplicate payments</h2>
      <p>If a payment fails but money is debited, or a duplicate payment is made, the amount is normally reversed automatically by the payment gateway/bank within the standard settlement time (usually 5&ndash;7 working days). If it is not, contact us at <a href="mailto:hello@schoozie.com">hello@schoozie.com</a> with the transaction reference and we will help resolve it.</p>

      <h2>4. How approved refunds are made</h2>
      <p>Approved refunds are made to the original payment method through the payment gateway. Timelines depend on the gateway and your bank, and are typically completed within 5&ndash;10 working days after approval.</p>

      <h2>5. How to request</h2>
      <p>Email <a href="mailto:hello@schoozie.com?subject=Refund%20Request">hello@schoozie.com</a> with the subject &ldquo;Refund Request&rdquo;, including your name, school, transaction reference/date and the reason. We aim to acknowledge within a few working days.</p>

